description:
&lt;p&gt;Staff Wellbeing Advisor (Band 5 - subject to Agenda for Change evaluation)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and motivated professional~Wellbeing Advisor to develop our health and wellbeing agenda as part of our People Strategy for the Shrewsbury and Telford Hospital Trust. It is important that our workforce have access to a variety of health and wellbeing guidance, advice and interventions to support them in their roles. The post-holder will be involved in leading on identifying health and wellbeing needs, co-ordinating plans, monitoring, reviewing and reporting on the outcomes of health and wellbeing plans and interventions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel that you are up to the challenge, have an understanding of health, wellbeing and engagement frameworks in the NHS and experience in a wide range of health and wellbeing initiatives including the planning and delivery of training then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful in the post you will also need project management and I.T skills. You will be able to demonstrate strong written and verbal communication skills with the ability to work confidently with teams and leaders at all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
